page.title: 05PLACE NAMES 3
page.content: place. The spa had/has a spa or spring. {Spring Wood}could be so called due to the presence of a spring or stream. It could perhaps be due to early budding trees. {Waskey Wood}is of uncertain etimology. The 'was' element means a wet place or swamp and comes from the Old English 'waesse'. Thus Waskey Wood could be on, or near boggy or wet ground. It could also could be from a personal name - Mr. Waskey's wood, indicating the owner of the wood. {East Holme House :}The word 'holm(e)' is used to describe low lying land by a river. Thishouse is sited on this type of land next to the Tees on its eastern bank. Thus the meaning is 'house on the low ground east of the river.
